@startuml
title Viaverse Chat / Messaging / Safety — Use Case Diagram
left to right direction

actor "Requester / Customer" as Customer
actor "Worker / Business" as Worker
actor "Moderator / Support" as Moderator
actor "Marketplace / Job" as Market
actor "Media / CDN" as Media
actor "Safety / Moderation" as Safety

rectangle "Chat / Messaging / Safety Boundary" {
  usecase "Open job conversation\ncontext-scoped" as Open
  usecase "Validate participants\njob/order permissions" as Participants
  usecase "Send message" as Send
  usecase "Deliver/read receipts" as Deliver
  usecase "Send attachment\nimage/video/file refs" as Attach
  usecase "Detect unsafe content\nPII/off-platform/payment" as Filter
  usecase "Block/warn/rate-limit" as Block
  usecase "Notify participants" as Notify
  usecase "Report conversation/message" as Report
  usecase "Moderator review\nscoped access" as Review
  usecase "Moderation action\nhide/delete/suspend" as Action
  usecase "Export chat for dispute\npolicy controlled" as Export
  usecase "Manage chat safety policy" as Policy
  usecase "Retention/deletion\nKVKK-aware" as Retention
  usecase "Emit events\nMessageSent\nChatReported" as Events
}

Customer --> Open
Worker --> Open
Open --> Participants
Participants --> Send
Send --> Deliver
Customer --> Attach
Worker --> Attach
Attach --> Filter
Send ..> Filter : text check
Filter ..> Block : if unsafe
Block --> Notify
Customer --> Report
Worker --> Report
Report --> Review
Moderator --> Review
Review --> Action
Action ..> Export : dispute/legal
Moderator --> Policy
Policy --> Retention
Retention --> Events
Market --> Open
Media --> Attach
Safety --> Filter

note bottom
Chat is job/order-context scoped.
Kişisel bilgi, off-platform payment, harassment, scam ve unsafe media için safety policy çalışır.
Matrix-like federation is not needed at launch; keep internal messaging modular.
end note
@enduml
